{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1b977c48-44d9-4254-8aee-12a104ef204f","content":"Here's what you need to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.v3.runner.mtp` package (xUnit v3) **or**, if staying on xUnit v2, add `xunit.runner.mtp` instead:\n\n   ```xml\n   <!-- For xUnit v2 (your current version): -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"*\" />\n\n   <!-- OR migrate to xUnit v3: -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3\" Version=\"*\" />\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3.runner.mtp\" Version=\"*\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Enable MTP** in your project file:\n\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   Or run the test executable directly (MTP produces a standalone executable).\n\n**Key notes:**\n- `TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport` ensures `dotnet test` uses MTP instead of VSTest.\n- If you're open to upgrading to **xUnit v3**, that's the recommended long-term path — it has native MTP support and additional features.\n- If staying on **xUnit v2.9.3**, the `xunit.runner.mtp` bridge package lets you use MTP without changing test code.\n\nWould you like help applying these changes to a specific project file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"69a88b3a-6700-4096-9129-914cf0abb6b5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":463,"requestId":"3430:2ADC27:749B627:80EBB12:69F3FA99"},"id":"7add9ca1-c9bc-4daa-9be4-0211da37bc8a","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00:58:10.628Z","parentId":"8aaf3d6a-2d18-4105-a9fa-4806fc554b58"}
